642. deos : the emperors from Augustus to Nero were of the house of Julius Caesar, who claimed descent from Iulus. It was usual to deify an emperor after his death, and they were often spoken of as deus even when alive. iure : “rightly shall all wars that are by fate destined to be, sink to rest beneath the race of Assaracus.⁷' It was the mission of the Romans to “war down” the world, and while Vergil was writing the Aeneia the temple of Janus was twice closed in sign of worldwide peace. For Assaracus, see V. 259.
